\begin_inset Formula $\lambda_{1}=635\pm10$
\end_inset

 nm and 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda_{2}=644\pm3$
\end_inset

 nm.
 The weighted average of the two values gives 
\begin_inset Formula $\bar{\lambda}=641\pm6$
\end_inset

 nm.
 This corresponds to a discrepancy of 
\begin_inset Formula $\sim1.3$
\end_inset

% with respect to the nominal value of 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda=632.8$
\end_inset

 nm.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
