 very similar to each other.
 This, however, is not apparent, either in the quantitative SSIM comparison
 (Figure 10) or by visual inspection (Figure 9).
 It appears that the patterns in general are simply more similar to their
 immediate neighbors, but there does not appear to be any surge in the SSIM
 index at separation distances of 40 cm.
 The reasons for this are not immediately apparent.
 The first three images appear to have a different texture than the other
 six, which is probably due to automatic adjustments made by the camera
 software, and variations in the distance from the camera to the screen.
 It is possible that the period of the wire mesh used was not actually 0.5
 mm, in which case the Talbot length would be different.
 A true period of 0.75 mm would imply that 
\begin_inset Formula $z_{T}\approx90$
\end_inset

